    <item>
      <title>1) European Researchers&#39; Night:</title>
      <link>/outreach/msca/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 05 Dec 2018 01:05:05 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>/outreach/msca/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;We demonstrated our project &amp;quot; robot that learns how to perform language instructions&amp;rdquo; in  ‘Science is Wonder-ful!’, on September 26-27 2018. Our project shows the ability of robots to understand spoken instructions which was working a noisy condition.You can see more details 
&lt;a href=&#34;/project/instructing_arm_robot/&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;here&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/img/msca3.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;(https://ec.europa.eu/research/mariecurieactions/)&#34;&#34;&gt;
I explained our project to Dimitrios Papadimoulis, Vice President of the European Parliament. (Image credit: 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://ec.europa.eu/research/mariecurieactions/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;European Comission - MSCA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/img/msca0.png&#34; alt=&#34;Mohammad Ali Zamani, Robot that understands spoken instructions&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/img/msca1.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Mohammad Ali Zamani, Robot that understands spoken instructions&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
